decision logic. The behavior of 'customer never sees' is verifiable by checking what the function returns; you don't need to test the HTTP layer or database persistence (those are covered by behavior 4).","test_description":"Unit test mocking the LLM to return two responses (initial_response, regenerated_response) and the tone classifier to flag the initial response as unsuitable. Call the response-selection function (or the main chatbot flow with mocked dependencies). Verify that the returned response to the caller is the regenerated_response, not the initial_response. Test variations: tone not flagged (return initial), tone flagged (return regenerated). Include a test verifying that if persistence is logged, the customer-facing response field contains only the final response.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13397,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13397},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a08bf35c-b0ca-461e-b64b-57329533ef00","uuid":"061a36a4-c7c5-42f2-bc5e-219e6acbda9f"}
